alled with parentheses, so I guess I'll need to keep that in mind as I proceed.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering potential issues**\\n\\nI’m thinking about the potential issue with `getDeclaredField` on a public static field in a native image. It still seems to fail if the field is registered as queried but isn't accessible. Good, it looks like the metadata in `fields` registers properly. I wonder about the condition `typeReached` for `GeneratedMessageLite$SerializedForm`. This class is reached through object creation, but do I need stats? Hmm, maybe not. Should I check `git diff`?\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_CxxTQQHIp4lj27757Z5G0IQY|fc_0be9edce1c5e5bcf0169f7a608b73081a1904b3c377fef2858", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git diff -- tests/src/com.typesafe.akka/akka-protobuf-v3_3/2.6.21/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_akka/akka_protobuf_v3_3/GeneratedMessageLiteInnerSerializedFormTest.scala tests/src/com.typesafe.akka/akka-protobuf-v3_3/2.6.21/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 814, "output": 1449, "cacheRead": 33280, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35543, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777837556572, "responseId": "resp_0be9edce1c5e5bcf0169f7a5f577a881a189e7ef19e03eebfc"}}
